tex:
The diagram shows a triangle $ABC$ and an arc with centre $C$ and radius $6.5\,\text{cm}$.

(a) **Using a straight edge and compasses only**, construct the locus of points inside the triangle that are equidistant from $BA$ and $BC$.


(b) Shade the region inside the triangle that is
    \begin{itemize}

(c) more than $6.5\,\text{cm}$ from $C$
    \end{itemize}
    and
    \begin{itemize}

(d) nearer to $BA$ than to $BC$.
    \end{itemize}

Solve the simultaneous equations.

You must show all your working.
\begin{align*}
    2x + 3y &= -12 \\
    5x + 2y &= 14
\end{align*}
